I like the dish and made it with rice pilaf. However, they left out one crucial step: dip the chicken into flour before the egg. Otherwise, the crust won't stay on the chicken. Make sure to have a bowl of flour on hand if you want this to resemble anything coated in breadcrumbs. My husband wants me to try it with pasta next time. The good thing about chicken is that it can go with just about any carb you choose.

