Rating: 3
This was a nice weekday recipe. I used the woman's marinade suggestion. My daughter liked it that way. However, for my husband and I, I used the scrapings from the chicken pan, added approx. 1/2 cup water, 1/4 cup lemon juice and 1 1/2 Tbl of sugar, and 1 tsp of lemon peel and boiled. Once that boiled, I added a corn starch/water mix (1 T/1T) and simmered until it thickened. It made a nice lemony sauce on top...husband scraped the pan for more.

